s="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-736i0" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">It would be bizarre if there were no factions within an organization.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block5" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-496na" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">Internal conflicts exist within any group—this Gu Nan was well aware of, but it was really the first time he'd seen someone like Daoist Lingyang, who talked about factions so openly.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block6" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-2sluu" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">However, the old Daoist quickly gave his explanation.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block7" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-8ahvd" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">One should know that all members of the Heaven-God Alliance were existences at the level of Star Rulers or gods, so they didn’t have a high demand for resources. Thus, it could be said that there were rarely any direct conflicts of interest.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block8" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-a18r0" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">In this case, instead of devolving into a chaotic mess, it would actually be better to divide the organization into clear factions, which would be more convenient for management and collaboration.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block9" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-ej00t" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">After all, factions didn't necessarily have to be in conflict with each other; they could also have a cooperative relationship.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block10" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-aeb8n" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">In Daoist Lingyang's vision, the future Heaven-God Alliance would exist in the form of an alliance of several major factions. This idea was also accepted by Xue Ren and Zi Luo Elder.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block11" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-edscd" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">"That doesn't sound too bad." Gu Nan was no stranger to this kind of organization. In fact, a certain well-known assassin organization also used a similar organizational framework.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block12" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-9gg1j" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">Since Gu Nan had no objections, Daoist Lingyang handed him a list of gods who had applied to join the Heaven-God Alliance.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block13" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-e17g9" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">"We need to assess the strength and goals of the applicants, mainly the latter," Daoist Lingyang explained.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block14" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-2nnhg" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">The strength of various gods wasn’t much of a secret. On the other hand, their motives for joining the Heaven-God Alliance warranted an investigation.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block15" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-ac658" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">"Assess them in what way?" Gu Nan asked while looking at the names on the list.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block16" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-dkpf4" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">"There are no restrictions. You can choose any method." Daoist Lingyang gave Gu Nan complete authority over the process. "It’s fine even if you forgo an assessment altogether and just recruit people directly.”</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block17" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-cm3av" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">"But if something goes wrong, I, the faction leader, will need to be responsible?" Gu Nan raised an eyebrow.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block18" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-2d5ou" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">"That's right. But ‘faction leader’ doesn’t sound very impressive, so I’ll have to think up a more imposing title in the future," Daoist Lingyang replied with a smile.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block19" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-40qv5" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">After knowing him for a while, one would realize that this old Daoist was actually quite a humorous person and wasn’t as old-fashioned as he looked.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block20" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-8itgt" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">Allowing core members to become leaders of their respective factions and developing new members by developing their factions wasn’t an inefficient choice.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block21" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-83toi" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">And to ensure that no one would add people indiscriminately, there was also a reasonable accountability system holding the core members responsible for their factions.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block22" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-evvpp" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">It was no wonder that the other core members were so slow with their assessments. Perhaps they never had any intention of adding too many people in the first place.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block23" type="h6"></div><h6 class="ZGnlH Y9Dpf OZy-3 lnyWN yMZv8w bCMSCT public-DraftStyleDefault-block-depth0 fixed-tab-size public-DraftStyleDefault-text-ltr" id="viewer-fa8av" style="line-height:1.5;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:13px"><span class="B2EFF public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr"><span style="font-size:18px">As gods from this side, they already had their own network, so they could just directly choose people from there.</span></span></h6><div data-hook="rcv-block24" type="h6"><